<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Beginner_BuildMode_UsefulObjects" s="314005">
  <T n="name">0x5DDD1474<!--String: "Useful Objects"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_UsefulObjects_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:91a9e6382da54adc</T>
      <T n="text">0xBDC170D6<!--String: "The most <b><font color='#199C2C'>essential</font></b> Objects help you care for your Sim’s <b><font color='#199C2C'>Needs</font></b>. A bed, toilet, shower, fridge, stove, counters, and an entertainment Object such as a TV or bookcase cover the basics!\n\nAs your Sim makes more money, it’s a good idea to buy more <b><font color='#199C2C'>expensive</font></b> versions of these Objects, as they fill Needs more <b><font color='#199C2C'>effectively</font></b>."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_UsefulObjects_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:91a9e6382da54adf</T>
      <T n="text">0xE8FBDA9F<!--String: "Objects that help you build <b><font color='#199C2C'>Skills</font></b> are also very useful. You can see which Skills an Object can raise in the Object’s <b><font color='#199C2C'>tooltip</font></b>.\n\nSome good <b><font color='#199C2C'>examples</font></b> are the chess table (Logic Skill), computer (Programming, Writing, Video Game Skills), mirror (Charisma Skill), instruments (Guitar, Violin, Piano Skills), bar (Mixology Skill), and garden pot (Gardening Skill).\n\nYou can find most Skill Objects in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Activities and Skills</font></b> category if you browse by Function."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_UsefulObjects_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:91a9e6382da54ade</T>
      <T n="text">0x8C1E50A6<!--String: "Here are some other <b><font color='#199C2C'>useful</font></b> Objects!\n\nA <b><font color='#199C2C'>trash can</font></b>, <b><font color='#199C2C'>sink</font></b>, and <b><font color='#199C2C'>fire alarm</font></b> will help your Sims keep their home clean and safe.\n\n<b><font color='#199C2C'>Dining or Desk Chairs</font></b> are required to use Objects such as Desks and Chess Tables. Make sure the Chair snaps to the Table when you place it!\n\n<b><font color='#199C2C'>Lights</font></b> will make it easier to see at night and nice <b><font color='#199C2C'>Decorations</font></b> will give your Sims Happy Moodlets."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
